inscription:
Ōta Nanpo: (Even a life that may be threatened by intestinal damage or venereal disease wishes to be saved, / at the time of cherry blossoms. / Shokusanjin);
Ishikawa Masamochi: (Immortals or goblins mistake / the branches of cherries at Yoshino / for banks of clouds. / Chikujuen);
Sugawara Nagane: (All white flowers of the world / look like kuzu at Mount Yoshino. / Nagane);
Kitagawa Kihei: (If the Ōmon of Yoshiwara could keep the wind from entering, / one thousand ryō would not be spared / to pay for a flower there. / Magao);
Kubo Shunman, LRC: (Please, lay monk, tie up the wind god / when the cherries at Yoshino are at their height.)
